<br>
Anyways, my question is where in that room do you typically set him up?<br>
<br>
My first thought is since the ae slow is so small range, you set up with the warrior having him face away from everyone else, AoW-style.  The mana-draining ae is so much longer range, it cant really be avoided as easily.  But at 1500 hp every 40 secs, its not that hard to just group heal.<br>
<br>
The trouble was he wasnt aginast a barrier, and kept getting moved.  The three things I can think to do are:<br>
<br>
1) Back him right up to the edge of the circle, and use that as your wall.  Trouble I see is he gets forced right onto the tank and you cant get he warrior far enough away from the tank to avoid the slow.<br>
<br>
2) walk him along the edge of the circle.  Its hard to heal a moving target ho,  maybe swtich directions every time he curses so your clerics can stay planted?<br>
<br>
3)  Up against the platform the shadow vortex spawns on.  However, my gut feeling is he will get shoved up on the platform, getting melees too close to the tank and getting tagged for 3600/slowed.<br>
<br>
The best sounding option to me at this point is walking him along the edge of the circle, and changing directions every time he casts the slow.  that keeps the slow off the melees, but lets the clerics stay standing and not have to case the tank around.  Extended range items for heals are a must too, since the 1500hp/500 mana ae (80) is almost as large as the range of CH or SL (100).<br>
<br>
