<br>
Very first time we did it, we didn't realize the portals were green in the room, so you can imagine the excessive adds we got but on the second run we won like that.<br>
<br>
After that we knew how to deal with the portals but Emmerik was a pain.  How we choose to initially do it was by charming the mobs in the room and basically using them to tank and obviously everyone else stood back and did damage from a distance.<br>
<br>
It worked, but it was way less than ideal because pets just cannot hold aggro at all.<br>
<br>
After that though I thought about the fight and made some changes. <br>
<br>
In your case I think you're making it more complex than it is, the fight vs Emmerik himself atleast.<br>
<br>
We switched to an actual MT engaging him, we don't really position him anywhere because no one else is attacking him except from a distance.  No healers are ever anywhere near the AOE no matter where he goes, and we don't use extended range items.  <br>
<br>
